Peiyu Chen

Bio

Peiyu Chen is a second-year MHS student in Cardiovascular and Clinical Epidemiology and a registered dietitian. Her research interests Include nutritional epidemiology and chronic diseases. Her thesis project investigates the association between dietary protein intake and incidence of dementia in ARIC study.

Education

Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health | Baltimore, MD

MHS in Epidemiology | August 2023 - May 2025

University of Michigan, School of Public Health | Ann Arbor, MI

MS in Nutritional Sciences | August 2017 - May 2019

University of Delaware | Newark, DE

B.S. in Dietetics | August 2013 - May 2017

Experience

Imperial, a Villa Center | Registered Dietitian | May 2020 - June 2022

Frankel Cardiovascular Center | Student Research Assistance | Feb 2018 - Apr 2019
